RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHAALEB'S DREAMS vied inside to the second turn, drew clear entering the stretch and held well while kept to task. MARIA'S GIFT vied two across to the second turn, swung out entering the stretch, fell back, continued willingly, couldn't gain and finished second best. C C'S WORLD was never far back, rallied into the second turn to loom a threat, angled in mid stretch, bid, came up empty and settled for show. ZENCHUA SKY raced in the back, went widest in the drive, lacked a stretch response and failed to threaten. MAIDEN ROCK went four wide on the first turn, fell back to trail the field and passed a tiring rival. TWELVE RED ROSES broke slowly, dropped inside to save ground, settled off the pace in a good position, had nothing left for the drive and stopped.
